China is set to complete its first blood bank for pandas, aiding in genetic diversity and research on blood types and transfusions.
The Qinling pandas, a sub-species of the giant panda, are facing threats from blooming bamboo, prompting conservation efforts.
China has applied to the UN to protect the pandas' habitat in Sichuan province.
Giant pandas in Gansu province are suffering from food shortages due to blooming arrow bamboo.
Efforts to protect and conserve the endangered species include establishing nature reserves and relocating pandas to safer habitats.
